<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
-As in the keys to genera and species. Size large and build elongate for genus. Pronotal disc with strongly incurved lateral carinae. In pronotal morphology species resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Platyverticula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyverticula ritchiei" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ritchiei">Platyverticula ritchiei</taxonomicName>
, but its genital structures are typical of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Chokwea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chokwea" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chokwea</taxonomicName>
. Coloration in subdued shades of brown and grey only.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
